Sentencas: The fully developed laminar flow and heat transfer for ducts with rectangular and trapezoidal cross-section in fuel cells have been numerically simulated with one porous wall with a uniform mass injection or suction, the other three walls being impermeable.
Titulo: Simulation of fully developed laminar heat and mass transfer in fuel cell ducts with different cross-sections

Sentencas: The new concept of thermal boundary conditions of combined constant heat flux and constant temperature on the walls was implemented.
Titulo: Simulation of fully developed laminar heat and mass transfer in fuel cell ducts with different cross-sections

Sentencas: Based on the constant thermal-physical property assumption, the wall friction factor and Nusselt number for different mass transfer rates, the aspect ratios and base angles are obtained.
Titulo: Simulation of fully developed laminar heat and mass transfer in fuel cell ducts with different cross-sections

Sentencas: Comparisons of these numerical results with published data are also presented.
Titulo: Simulation of fully developed laminar heat and mass transfer in fuel cell ducts with different cross-sections
